Sentencas: A series of Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-delta-Ag cermets with different Ag contents were prepared by conventional sintering process aiming at assessing the suitability of using them as cathode material for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) with Gadolinia-doped ceria electrolyte.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of gadolinia-doped ceria-silver cermet cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The chemical compatibility between Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-delta (CGO) and Ag was investigated by X-ray diffraction, scanning electron microscopy and X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of gadolinia-doped ceria-silver cermet cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thermal expansion coefficients of the cermets were measured as a function of Ag content and were found to increase with metallic content.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of gadolinia-doped ceria-silver cermet cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Although oxygen adsorption at the surface of the cermets could be detected, no reaction or solid solubility between CGO and Ag was found.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of gadolinia-doped ceria-silver cermet cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells
